en: Welcoming Etta Moten Barnett to Knoxville, Tennessee

1 tif Austin High School principal Thomas R. Davis (pictured foreground, left of center, outside the school), along with local students of all ages, welcomes to Knoxvilles Vine Street of the 1940s the influential star of stage and screen, actress-singer Etta Moten Barnett (pictured center with flowers). Earlier that decade, Etta Moten had taken over the female lead in the revival of Porgy and Bess.
